Class Stopwatch

  • java.lang.Object
    • Stopwatch

  • public class Stopwatch
extends java.lang.Object
    Measures elapsed time in miliseconds.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Josiah Richards

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      Stopwatch()
      Create a new Stopwatch with 0 milliseconds elapsed.
      Stopwatch(long elapsedTime)
      Create a new Stopwatch with given amount of milliseconds already elapsed.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      long getElapsedTime()
      Gets the time elapsed from when the timer was started and paused + any elapsed time before that.
      void pause()
      Pausing/stops the stopwatch, updating the elapsed time since the stopwatch was started.
      void reset()
      Resets the stopwatch so that it's no longer timing and that 0 milliseconds have elapsed.
      void restart()
      Resets the stopwatch and then starts it again.
      void setElapsedTime(long elapsedTime)
      Forces the elapsed time to be a value.
      void start()
      Start counting elapsed milliseconds.
